---
metaDescription: How Ryan McGovern uses AI as a developer — tools, principles, and transparency.
---

## My Stance

I embrace AI as a tool that augments my work. It's woven into my daily workflow across coding, content creation, research, and social media. But I maintain a firm principle: **AI assists, I decide.** Every piece of output is reviewed and approved by me before it goes anywhere.

I don't use unchecked or autonomous mode with any AI agents. I acknowledge the broader implications of AI — the environmental costs, the economic shifts, the questions it raises about creative work. Using AI responsibly means being transparent about it, which is why this page exists.

## How I Use AI

### Code

AI-assisted at minimum. Claude Code and OpenAI Codex are core parts of my development workflow — from scaffolding and debugging to refactoring and code review.

### Content

Blog posts and my about page may be AI-prompted or lightly assisted, but are not fully AI-generated. I use AI to help organize thoughts, draft outlines, and refine language, but the ideas and editorial decisions are mine.

### Social Media

My social posts are almost always AI-generated, typically drafted from my notes or ideas and refined through conversation with an AI tool.

### Research

AI is a regular part of how I explore new technologies, understand documentation, and investigate solutions.

## Tools

- **Claude / Claude Code** — Primary AI assistant for development and content
- **ChatGPT / Codex** — Used for development, research, and content drafting

I don't currently use AI image generation tools.

## Principles

- All AI output is reviewed and approved before publishing
- AI assists, human decides — no unchecked autonomous agents
- Transparency about AI usage (hence this page)
- Acknowledgment of environmental and economic impacts

